I did like the location because we could just park in a parking garage and then walk or take public transportation if we wanted.	As I was rushing to work each morning it made life SO much easier than trying to find parking or pay way too much for a garage 10 blocks away.	We checked in with many bags and were not offered help from the valets or the front desk with carrying the bags or offering a trolly to push them to our room.	Valet parking was an added cost that I was not expecting, but it wasn't so bad - and I really enjoyed having my car pulled around for me and put away for me.